{
  "text": "The flavin-mononucleotide-dependent enzyme O 2 -insensitive NADPH nitroreductase dihydropteridine reductase, involved in co-factor biosynthesis, was also significantly upregulated at pH 6.4; although its function in assisting growth remains unclear, it should be noted that it was also upregulated (3.2-fold) in S. oralis following growth at pH 5.5 [CITATION_1] .",
